sd=Customer Reference Data Management	This service domain maintains a range customer relationship reference information covering aspects including general reference details, contacts and associations and demographic information	Customer reference details are accessed to pre-populate an application form for a new product opportunity with the customer	The customer reference data service domain maintains a potentially wide range of customer reference data that might be used in any interaction between the bank and the customer including relationship development, sales/marketing, servicing and product delivery. This can include general reference and contact details, customer associations, demographic details and some servicing preferences. Different information may be maintained for different customer types such as consumers and corporates
sdpath=customer-reference-data-management
crpath=customer-reference-data-directory-entry
crr=Customer Reference Data Directory Entry Instance
mcr=Customer Reference Data Directory Entry
bqs=Reference Associations Demographics BankRelations
